00:10:27.943 --> 00:10:30.360
the technology is going to
have a hard time being adopted.

00:10:30.360 --> 00:10:30.750
GARY GENSLER: Right.

00:10:30.750 --> 00:10:31.410
Right.

00:10:31.410 --> 00:10:34.810
So of course we want to protect
against fraud in the capital

00:10:34.810 --> 00:10:35.310
markets.

00:10:35.310 --> 00:10:37.410
We also want to protect
against manipulation

00:10:37.410 --> 00:10:39.480
and ensure investment
protection.

00:10:39.480 --> 00:10:41.850
And we've seen,
particularly in some fields

00:10:41.850 --> 00:10:43.710
like cryptocurrencies,
that they're

00:10:43.710 --> 00:10:48.940
rife with fraud and manipulation
and sort of quick buck artists,

00:10:48.940 --> 00:10:50.910
frankly, around the globe.

00:10:50.910 --> 00:10:54.840
And so to ensure that
any long-term viability

00:10:54.840 --> 00:10:57.420
of a project, real
viability comes

00:10:57.420 --> 00:11:01.800
with investor protection,
consumer protection norms,

00:11:01.800 --> 00:11:07.890
as well as norms about fairness,
inclusiveness, explainability,

00:11:07.890 --> 00:11:08.770
and the like.

00:11:08.770 --> 00:11:11.730
In most nations, these are
embedded in various regulations

00:11:11.730 --> 00:11:12.570
and laws.

00:11:12.570 --> 00:11:18.030
So standing up a new
effort, whether it's inside

00:11:18.030 --> 00:11:21.780
of an incumbent, inside
a big tech, or a startup,

00:11:21.780 --> 00:11:24.450
